              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value based on the input parameters provided. This function is designed to return a description for a specific meter read type, which is identified by an input parameter. The function maps a code or identifier to a human-readable description, facilitating better understanding and reporting of meter read types."
